H0.text: In the 18th Century, Russia led a coalition that defeated which country in the Great Northern War. Poland

H1.text: In the 18th Century, Russia led a coalition that defeated which country in the Great Northern War. Denmark

H2.text: In the 18th Century, Russia led a coalition that defeated which country in the Great Northern War. Saxony

H3.text: In the 18th Century, Russia led a coalition that defeated which country in the Great Northern War. SWEDEN

A4.text: The war ended with the defeat of Sweden, leaving Russia as the new dominant power in the Baltic region and as a new major force in European politics.

A5.text: By these treaties Sweden ceded its exemption from the Sound Dues and lost the Baltic provinces and the southern part of Swedish Pomerania.
